DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-3878(92)90021-Z
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/030438789290021Z
AB  - We examine the impact of restrictive trade regimes on wages in the manufacturing sector. A simple three-sector economic model predicts that wages will fall in response to trade regime restrictiveness. Empirical tests are based on data for 37 countries over time. Our measure of trade regime restrictiveness is the black market premium on U.S. dollars. The results strongly suggest that restrictive trade regimes reduce wages, consistent with our theoretical analysis.
