AB  - This paper investigates empirically the relationship between export growth and GNP growth using Urquhart's (1988) annual Canadian data from 1870–1985. In particular, the study investigates whether knowledge of past export growth improves the prediction of future GNP growth beyond predictions that are based on past GNP growth alone. This is the empirical definition of Granger causality.
