AB  - The specific-factors model is employed in this paper as a means of explaining how economic development may serve to diminish women's welfare. Three changes associated with the development process are analyzed for their effect on women's real and relative wage: (1) an expansion of trade induced by an improvement in the terms of trade. (2) technological change, and (3) an increase in female labor force participation.
